Based on everything I've seen across our conversations — the entity design, domain modeling, architecture decisions, and how you think     
  about features — here's my honest assessment:                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                             
  Score: 72/100 (Solid Mid-Level, Trending Senior)                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                             
  What you're doing well (strengths):                                                                                                        
                                                            
  Domain Modeling — 8/10                                                                                                                     
  - Your fuel station domain is well-decomposed: Tanks, Pumps, Nozzles, Products, GradeTypes, OilTypes — each has a clear purpose
  - The relationships make sense (Tank → Product, Nozzle → Pump, InvoiceBill → Customer/Vehicle)                                             
  - Multi-tenancy via BaseEntity with scid is a smart pattern for a multi-site SaaS             
                                                                                                                                             
  Layered Architecture — 7/10                                                                                                                
  - Clean Controller → Service → Repository separation, consistently applied                                                                 
  - REST API conventions are solid (/api/<resource>, proper HTTP methods, status codes)                                                      
                                                            
  Full-Stack Ownership — 8/10                                                                                                                
  - You're building both backend and frontend, handling deployment (EC2/ECS/S3), database design, and even planning ML — that's a rare
  breadth                                                                                                                                    
                                                            
  Business Thinking — 8/10                                                                                                                   
  - Credit/payment system, shift-based operations, inventory tracking, TNEB bill parsing — you understand the real business deeply, not just 
  the code                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                             
  Where you can grow:                                                                                                                        
                                                            
  Database Design — 6/10                                                                                                                     
  - Using ddl-auto: update with no migrations is risky for production — one bad entity change can corrupt data (closer to production)
  - No database indexes beyond PKs/FKs (queries on status, scid, date fields will slow down as data grows)  (working)                                  
  - Missing unique constraints where needed (e.g., employeeCode should probably be unique) (working)               
                                                                                                                                             
  Validation & Error Handling — 5/10  (done)                                                                                                         
  - No @Valid / Bean Validation annotations on entities — validation lives only in frontend                                                  
  - Backend accepts any JSON without checking required fields, field lengths, or formats                                                     
  - RuntimeException used everywhere — no custom exception classes or global @ControllerAdvice                                               
                                                                                                                                             
  Security — 5/10                                                                                                                          
  - No authentication/authorization yet (Cognito planned but not implemented)                                                                
  - Password fields exposed in API responses (you know about this one)      (done)                                                                 
  - No rate limiting, no input sanitization on the backend side        (done)                                                           
                                                                                                                                             
  Testing — 3/10 (done)                                                                                                                            
  - I haven't seen any unit or integration tests. For a production app managing money (invoices, payments, credit), this is the biggest gap  
                                                                                                                                             
  Code Organization — 6/10 (done)                                                                                                                   
  - employee-list.tsx at 1000+ lines doing table + forms + profile + salary + advances + documents — this should be split into smaller       
  components                                                                                                                                 
  - Some duplication in upload handlers (photo/aadhar/pan are nearly identical — could be one generic function)                              
                                                                                                                                             
  Roadmap to 85+:                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                             
  1. Add Flyway/Liquibase — replace ddl-auto: update with proper migrations (when we closer to production deploy)                                                                 
  2. Add @ControllerAdvice + custom exceptions — proper error responses (done)                                                                 
  3. Write tests — even just service-layer tests for payment/invoice logic (done)                                                               
  4. Split large components — ProfileModal, EmployeeForm, DocumentsTab as separate files (done)                                                  
  5. Add Bean Validation — @NotBlank, @Email, @Size on entities (done)                                                                              
                                                                                                                                             
  You're building a real, complex production application solo — that already puts you ahead of many developers. The gaps are mostly in       
  production hardening, not in design thinking.  

